    "Compared to repeated runs, this approach is more efficient because training is done only once.",
    "However, it requires models that explicitly support conditional sampling (e.g., GAIN, MI-WAE, diffusion-based imputers).",
    "The technical challenge is deciding how many samples to draw: too few gives noisy estimates of variability, while too many increases the runtime without much benefit.",
